law.text:
The Secretary of State shall report annually on or before June 30 to the Governor and to the Legislative Research Commission on the operation of the filing office. The report must contain a statement of the extent to which:
The filing-office administrative regulations are not in harmony with the rules of filing offices in other jurisdictions that enact substantially this part of this article and the reasons for these variations; and
The filing-office administrative regulations are not in harmony with the most recent version of the Model Rules promulgated by the International Association of Corporate Administrators, or any successor organization, and the reasons for these variations.
law.history: Created 2000 Ky. Acts ch. 408, sec. 118, effective July 1, 2001.
